\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Diagonals:}{\fs20\cf0 
 When measuring distance, the first diagonal counts as 1 square, the second counts as 2 squares, the third counts as 1, the fourth as 2, and so on.
\par You can\rquote t move diagonally past a corner (even by taking a 5-foot step). You can move diagonally past a creature, even an opponent.
\par You can also move diagonally past other impassable obstacles, such as pits.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Closest Creature:}{\fs20\cf0  When it\rquote s important to determine the closest square or creature to a location, if two squares or creatures are equally close, randomly determine which one counts as closest by rolling a die.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Moving through a Square
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Friend:}{\fs20\cf0 
 You can move through a square occupied by a friendly character, unless you are charging. When you move through a square occupied by a friendly character, that character doesn\rquote t provide you with cover.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Opponent:}{\fs20\cf0  You can\rquote 
t move through a square occupied by an opponent, unless the opponent is helpless. You can move through a square occupied by a helpless opponent without penalty. (Some creatures, particularly very large ones, 
may present an obstacle even when helpless. In such cases, each square you move through counts as 2 squares.)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Ending Your Movement:}{\fs20\cf0  You can\rquote t end your movement in the same square as another creature unless it is helpless.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Overrun:}{\fs20\cf0  During your movement you can attempt to move through a square occupied by an opponent.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Tumbling:}{\fs20\cf0  A trained character can attempt to tumble through a square occupied by an opponent (see the Tumble skill).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Very Small Creature:}{\fs20\cf0  A Fine, Diminutive, or Tiny creature can move into or through an occupied square. The creature provokes attacks of opportunity when doing so.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Square Occupied by Creature Three Sizes Larger or Smaller:}{\fs20\cf0  Any creature can move through a square occupied by a creature three size categories larger than it is.
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs18\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 A big creature can move through a square occupied by a creature three size categories smaller than it is.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Designated Exceptions:}{\fs20\cf0  Some creatures break th
e above rules. A creature that completely fills the squares it occupies cannot be moved past, even with the Tumble skill or similar special abilities.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Terrain and Obstacles
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Difficult Terrain: }{\fs20\cf0 Difficult terrain hampers movement. Each square of difficult te
rrain counts as 2 squares of movement. (Each diagonal move into a difficult terrain square counts as 3 squares.) You can\rquote t run or charge across difficult terrain.
\par If you occupy squares with different kinds of terrain, you can move only as fast as the most difficult terrain you occupy will allow.
\par Flying and incorporeal creatures are not hampered by difficult terrain.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Obstacles:}{\fs20\cf0  Like difficult terrain, obstacles can hamper movement. If an obstacle hampers movement but doesn\rquote t completely block it each obstruct
ed square or obstacle between squares counts as 2 squares of movement. You must pay this cost to cross the barrier, in addition to the cost to move into the square on the other side. If you don\rquote 
t have sufficient movement to cross the barrier and move into the square on the other side, you can\rquote t cross the barrier. Some obstacles may also require a skill check to cross.
\par On the other hand, some obstacles block movement entirely. A character can\rquote t move through a blocking obstacle.
\par Flying and incorporeal creatures can avoid most obstacles
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Squeezing:}{\fs20\cf0  In some cases, you may have to squeeze into or through an area that isn\rquote 
t as wide as the space you take up. You can squeeze through or into a space that is at least half as wide as your normal space. Each move into or through a narrow space counts as if it were 2 squares, and while squeezed in a narrow space you take a 
\endash 4 penalty on attack rolls and a \endash 4 penalty to AC.
\par When a Large creature (which normally takes up four squares) squeezes into a space that\rquote s one square wide, the creature\rquote 
s miniature figure occupies two squares, centered on the line between the two squares. For a bigger creature, center the creature likewise in the area it squeezes into.
\par A creature can squeeze past an opponent while moving but it can\rquote t end its movement in an occupied square.
\par To squeeze through or into a space less than half your space\rquote s width, you must use the Escape Artist skill. You can\rquote t attack while using Escape Artist to squeeze through or into a narrow space, you take a \endash 4 penalty to
 AC, and you lose any Dexterity bonus to AC.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Special Movement Rules
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs18\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 These rules cover special movement situations.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Accidentally Ending Movement in an Illegal Space:}{\fs20\cf0 
 Sometimes a character ends its movement while moving through a space where it\rquote s not allowed to stop. When that happens, put your miniature in the last legal position you occupied, or the closest legal position, if there\rquote 
s a legal position that\rquote s closer.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Double Movement Cost:}{\fs20\cf0  When your movement is hampered in some way, your movement usually cost
s double. For example, each square of movement through difficult terrain counts as 2 squares, and each diagonal move through such terrain counts as 3 squares (just as two diagonal moves normally do).
\par If movement cost is doubled twice, then each square coun
