\par CONCEALMENT
\par }{\fs20\cf0 To determine whether your target has concealment from your ranged attack, choose a corner of your square. If any line from this corner to any corner of the target\rquote 
s square passes through a square or border that provides concealment, the target has concealment.
\par When making a melee attack against an adjacent target, your target has concealment if his space is entirely within an effect that grants concealment. When making a melee attack against a target that isn\rquote 
t adjacent to you use the rules for determining concealment from ranged attacks.
\par In addition, some magical effects provide concealment against all attacks, regardless of whether any intervening concealment exists.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Concealment Miss Chance: }{\fs20\cf0 
Concealment gives the subject of a successful attack a 20% chance that the attacker missed because of the concealment. If the attacker hits, the defender must make a miss chance percentile roll to avoid be
ing struck. Multiple concealment conditions do not stack.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Concealment and Hide Checks:}{\fs20\cf0  You can use concealment to make a Hide check. Without concealment, you usually need cover to make a Hide check.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Total Concealment:}{\fs20\cf0  If you have line of effect to a target but not line of sight he is considered to have total concealment from you. You can\rquote 
t attack an opponent that has total concealment, though you can attack into a square that you think he occupies. A successful attack into a square occupied by an enemy with
 total concealment has a 50% miss chance (instead of the normal 20% miss chance for an opponent with concealment).
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs18\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 You can\rquote 
t execute an attack of opportunity against an opponent with total concealment, even if you know what square or squares the opponent occupies.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Ignoring Concealment:}{\fs20\cf0  Concealment isn\rquote t always effective. A shadowy area or darkness doesn\rquote 
t provide any concealment against an opponent with darkvision. Characters with low-light vision can see clearly for a greater distance with the same light s
ource than other characters. Although invisibility provides total concealment, sighted opponents may still make Spot checks to notice the location of an invisible character. An invisible character gains a +20 bonus on Hide checks if moving, or a +40 bonus
 on Hide checks when not moving (even though opponents can\rquote t see you, they might be able to figure out where you are from other visual clues).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Varying Degrees of Concealment:}{\fs20\cf0  Certain situations may provide more or less than typical concealment, and modify the miss chance accordingly.
\par }{\cf0 
\par FLANKING
\par }{\fs20\cf0 When making a melee attack, you get a +2 flanking bonus if your opponent is threatened by a character or creature friendly to you on the opponent\rquote s opposite border or opposite corner.
\par When in doubt about whether two friendly characters flank an opponent in the middle, trace an imaginary line between the two friendly characters\rquote  centers. If the line passes through opposite borders of the opponent\rquote 
s space (including corners of those borders), then the opponent is flanked.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Exception: }{\fs20\cf0 If a flanker takes up more than 1 square, it gets the flanking bonus if any square it occupies counts for flanking.
\par Only a creature or character that threatens the defender can help an attacker get a flanking bonus.
\par Creatures with a reach of 0 feet can\rquote t flank an opponent.
\par }{\cf0 
\par HELPLESS DEFENDERS
\par }{\fs20\cf0 A helpless opponent is someone who is bound, sleeping, paralyzed, unconscious, or otherwise at your mercy.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Regular Attack:}{\fs20\cf0  A helpless character takes a \endash 4 penalty to AC against melee attacks, but no penalty to AC against ranged attacks.
\par A helpless defender can\rquote t use any Dexterity bonus to AC. In fact, his Dexterity score is treated as if it were 0 and his Dexterity modifier to AC as if it were \endash 5 (and a rogue can sneak attack him).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Coup de Grace:}{\fs20\cf0  As a full-round action, you can use a melee weapon to deliver a coup de grace to a helpless opponent. You can also use a bow or crossbow, provided you are adjacent to the target.
\par You automatically hit and score a critical hit. If the defender survives the damage, he must make a Fortitude save (DC 10 + damage dealt) or die. A rogue also gets her extra sneak attack damage against a helpless opponent when delivering a coup de grace.

\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs18\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 Delivering a coup de grace provokes attacks of opportunity from threatening opponents.
