\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Being Tripped (Prone):}{\fs20\cf0  A tripped character is prone. Standing up is a move action.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Tripping a Mounted Opponent:}{\fs20\cf0  You may make a trip attack against a mounted opponent. The defender may make a Ride check in place of his Dexterity or Strength check. If you succeed, you pull the rider from his mount.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Tripping with a Weapon:}{\fs20\cf0  Some weapons can be used to make trip attacks. In this case, you make a melee touch attack with the weapon instead of an unarmed melee touch attack, and you don\rquote t provoke an attack of opportunity.

