\par Evil Clerics and Undead
\par Evi
l clerics channel negative energy to rebuke (awe) or command (control) undead rather than channeling positive energy to turn or destroy them. An evil cleric makes the equivalent of a turning check. Undead that would be turned are rebuked instead, and thos
e that would be destroyed are commanded.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Rebuked:}{\fs20\cf0  A rebuked undead creature cowers as if in awe (attack rolls against the creature get a +2 bonus). The effect lasts 10 rounds.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Commanded:}{\fs20\cf0  A commanded undead creature is under the mental control of the evil cl
eric. The cleric must take a standard action to give mental orders to a commanded undead. At any one time, the cleric may command any number of undead whose total Hit Dice do not exceed his level. He may voluntarily relinquish command on any commanded und
ead creature or creatures in order to command new ones.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Dispelling Turning:}{\fs20\cf0  An evil cleric may channel negative energy to dispel a good cleric\rquote s turning effect. The evil cleric makes a turning check as if attempting to rebuke the undead. If the turning chec
k result is equal to or greater than the turning check result that the good cleric scored when turning the undead, then the undead are no longer turned. The evil cleric rolls turning damage of 2d6 + cleric level + Charisma modifier to see how many Hit Dic
e worth of undead he can affect in this way (as if he were rebuking them).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bolstering Undead:}{\fs20\cf0  An evil cleric may also bolster undead creatures against turning in advance. He makes a turning check as if attempting to rebuke the undead, but the Hit Dice resul
t on Table: Turning Undead becomes the undead creatures\rquote  effective Hit Dice as far as turning is concerned (provided the result is higher than the creatures\rquote 
 actual Hit Dice). The bolstering lasts 10 rounds. An evil undead cleric can bolster himself in this manner.
\par 
\par Neutral Clerics and Undead
\par A cleric of neutral alignment can either turn undead but not rebuke them, or rebuke undead but not turn them. See Turn or Rebuke Undead for more information.
\par Even if a cleric is neutral, channeling positive energy is a good act and channeling negative energy is evil.
\par 
\par Paladins and Undead
\par Beginning at 4th level, paladins can turn undead as if they were clerics of three levels lower than they actually are.
\par 
\par Turning Other Creatures
\par Some clerics have the ability to turn creatures other than undead.
\par The turning check result is determined as normal.
